\f0\b \cf2 IV.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 OOBC PLANS FOR 2025-2028
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC has outlined a 
\f0\b comprehensive plan\cf3 \super \ul [18]
\f1\b0 \cf2 \nosupersub \ulnone  for the period 2025-2028, focusing on promoting the welfare and development of the OBCs. This plan is anchored in the principle of \'93Moral Governance\'94 and driven by the core values of the office. The plan prioritizes several key areas:\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 1.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Gathering Information and Assessing Needs:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC will conduct comprehensive mapping and needs assessments of OBCs through the 
\f0\b OBC-MANA
\f1\b0  program. This program will involve developing 
\f0\b baseline studies
\f1\b0  for research and policy-making as well as community 
\f0\b socio-economic profiling
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b survey
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b key information assessment
\f1\b0  reviews to gain a deeper understanding of the conditions and needs of these communities. Additionally, the OOBC will establish and improve a 
\f0\b database management system
\f1\b0  to ensure accurate and reliable data collection and analysis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 2.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Policy Recommendation and Program Development:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Based on the gathered information and needs assessments, the OOBC will recommend policies, programs, and services to the Chief Minister that are specifically tailored to address the needs of OBCs. This includes ensuring data-driven policy recommendations and submitting comprehensive proposals to the Chief Minister for approval.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 3.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Strengthening Coordination and Collaboration:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC will strengthen its coordination mechanisms with various stakeholders, including ministries, agencies, and offices within BARMM, local government units, national government agencies, and development partners. This will involve conducting regular forums and meetings, establishing an OBC council, and implementing the SMART program (Stronger Moro Advocacy on Rehabilitation and Transformation) to ensure effective and efficient collaboration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 4.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Institutional Strengthening and Capacity Building:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC will focus on internal capacity building through technical learning and development programs for its personnel. This includes supervisor and executive development training, completed staff work (CSW) training, research and policy making trainings, community organizing and development training, benchmarking exercises, and other capacity building initiatives to improve organizational performance and effectiveness.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 5.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Monitoring, Evaluation, and Reporting:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC will establish a robust monitoring and evaluation system to track the progress and impact of its recommended policies, programs, and services. This includes conducting regular M&E activities, formulating and submitting reports, and ensuring transparency and accountability.\
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\fi-480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 6.
\f2\b0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\f0\b\fs32 Strategic Communication:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li480\fi480\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The OOBC will strengthen its information drive and public outreach efforts through various initiatives, including online talk shows, social media engagement, and the printing and distribution of information and education campaign (IEC) materials. This will raise awareness about the OOBC's mandate and activities and ensure effective communication with stakeholders and the public.\
